name: Plank
explanation: Start in a high plank (aka push-up) position. Bend your elbows and rest your weight on your forearms instead of your hands. Your body should form a straight line from your shoulders to your ankles. Brace your core as if you were about to be punched in the stomach. (Don't forget to breathe.)

name: Knee Plank
explanation: Lay face down on the ground with extended legs. Point your toes while you place your hands beneath your shoulders. Push yourself up into the plank position. Maintaining a tight core and flat back, bring your left knee to your right elbow.

name: Straight Arm Knee Plank
explanation: Get into plank position by supporting your body weight on your hands and toes. Hands should be placed directly under your shoulders.  Push yourself up into the plank position. Maintaining a tight core and flat back, bring your left knee to your right elbow.

name: Kneeling Side Plank Right
explanation: Lie on your side supporting yourself on your forearm and your knees, rather than your feet. Engage your core and hold a straight line from your knees to your head – don't let your hips sag

name: Kneeling Side Plank Left
explanation: Lie on your side supporting yourself on your forearm and your knees, rather than your feet. Engage your core and hold a straight line from your knees to your head – don't let your hips sag
